\begin{frame}
  \frametitle{Python Flask}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Flask is a micro web framework written in Python. \pause
  \item  It is classified as a micro framework because it does not require particular tools or libraries.\pause
  \item Easy to learn and simple to use, enabling you to build your web app in a short amount of time.\pause 
  \item Flask is a small and powerful web framework for Python. %leave out the \pause on the final item
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

% \section{Main Body} % add these to see outline in slides

\begin{frame}
  \frametitle{Features...}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Built-in development server and fast debugger.
  \item Unicode based
  \item Flask has a lightweight and modular design, so it easy to transform it to the web framework you need with a few extensions.
  \item HTTP request handling functionality%leave out the \pause on the final item
  \item High Flexibility
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}


\begin{frame}
  \frametitle{How does this works?}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item simple log-in page. 
  \item Enter the page using valid user name and password.
  \item Entering the incorrect credentials, then press login this will lead to a error response: “Error: Invalid Credentials. Please try again.”
  \item Now the correct username and password will redirected to the / URL.
  \item Now it leads to a Web page with Home page and Welocome page.
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}
 \frametitle{Procedure}
 \begin{itemize}
 \item Created a directory with two Sub directories template and static . 
 \item Python file having the main source is created inside the main directory .
 \item Template contains HTML Codes for creating Homepage and Welcome page.
 \item Static contains the Bootstrap program for the structuring of the pages .
 \item These HTML files are fetched to the Python program using render-template with function return.
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{CONCLUSION}
Now that users have the ability to login, we need to protect that URL / from unauthorized access. In other words, when an end user hits that endpoint, unless they are already logged in, then they should be immediately sent to the login page. 
\end{frame}
